<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" ?>
<resources>

  <style name="DrawerArrowStyle" parent="@style/Widget.AppCompat.DrawerArrowToggle">
    <item name="spinBars">true</item>
    <item name="color">#FFFFFF</item>
  </style>

  <style name="MainTheme" parent="MainTheme.Base">
    As of Xamarin.Forms 4.6 the theme has moved into the Forms binary
    If you want to override anything you can do that here.
    Underneath are a couple of entries to get you started.

    Set theme colors from https://aka.ms/material-colors
    colorPrimary is used for the default action bar background
    <!--<item name="colorPrimary">#1B0E7A</item>
     colorPrimaryDark is used for the status bar 
    <item name="colorPrimaryDark">#13095E</item>
     colorAccent is used as the default value for colorControlActivated
         which is used to tint widgets 
    <item name="colorAccent">#F37A27</item>-->
  </style>


  <!-- Base theme applied no matter what API -->
  <style name="MainTheme.Base" parent="Theme.AppCompat.Light.DarkActionBar">
    <!--If you are using revision 22.1 please use just windowNoTitle. Without android:-->
    <item name="windowNoTitle">true</item>
    <!--We will be using the toolbar so no need to show ActionBar-->
    <item name="windowActionBar">false</item>
    <!-- Set theme colors from https://aka.ms/material-colors -->
    <!-- colorPrimary is used for the default action bar background -->
    <item name="colorPrimary">#9E079E</item>
    <!-- colorPrimaryDark is used for the status bar -->
    <item name="colorPrimaryDark">#8949C3</item>
    <!-- colorAccent is used as the default value for colorControlActivated
         which is used to tint widgets -->

    <!--turn button text to smallCaps-->
    <item name="android:textAllCaps">false</item>
    <!--just stops here-->

    <item name="colorControlActivated">#EFBB17</item>
    <item name="colorAccent">#EFBB17</item>
    <!-- You can also set colorControlNormal, colorControlActivated
         colorControlHighlight and colorSwitchThumbNormal. -->
    <item name="colorSwitchThumbNormal">#FFFFFF</item>
    <item name="colorControlHighlight">#DED8E5</item>
    <item name="colorControlNormal">#FFFFFF</item>
    <item name="drawerArrowStyle">@style/DrawerArrowStyle</item>
    <item name="windowActionModeOverlay">true</item>
    <item name="android:colorActivatedHighlight">#DED8E5</item>

    <item name="android:datePickerDialogTheme">@style/AppCompatDialogStyle</item>
  </style>

  <!--<style name="fontForTheWholeApp">
        <item name="android:textStyle">none</item>
        <item name="android:fontFamily">Poppins-Regular</item>
        <item name="android:padding">2dip</item>
    </style>-->

  <style name="AppCompatDialogStyle" parent="Theme.AppCompat.Light.Dialog">
    <item name="colorAccent">#9E079E</item>
  </style>
</resources>